result.execSummary:
The defendant Reggie Duane Gilbertson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Reggie Duane Gilbertson is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Reggie Duane Gilbertson was found guilty of Possession of Methamphetamine [Modifiers: Penalties for Felonies-Class "I" Felony], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(g).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

CO: Lundell, RPR: Val Deiss, Clerk: Fox, ADA: Edward Minser, DF ATTY:  T Gregory Amann, DF:  Reggie Duane Gilbertson appeared from jail.   Court reviews constitutional rights and felony conviction with def. Court finds def freely, voluntarily and knowingly waives rights. Court reads charge and possible penalties for count one (possess of meth). Def pleads no contest. Court uses complaints/reports as factual basis, accepts plea and adjudicates Def guilty of count one. Court dismisses count 2. Sentencing recommendations. Court orders: 
- 345 days in the St. Croix County jail with good time; concurrent to any sentence currently serving. Def to receive 259 days credit for time served.
- Court costs $268.00. Probation to collect while defendant is on Extended Supervision. 
- DNA surcharge $250.00. Probation to collect while defendant is on Extended Supervision. 
Def advised of right to appeal.
